00:19:34.160 --> 00:19:39.280
<b>我能做的不止是打打杀杀 我想让人看到这点
<b>I can do more than this. And people need to see that.</b></b>


142
00:19:42.720 --> 00:19:47.730
<b>那 你想向世界展示自己?
<b>So what is it that you are passionate about showing the world?</b></b>


143
00:19:47.760 --> 00:19:50.960
<b>可你只会打打杀杀啊
<b>This is the only thing you can do.</b></b>


144
00:19:53.320 --> 00:19:56.040
<b>我还可以弄个花圃
<b>I could plant a garden.</b></b>


145
00:19:57.400 --> 00:20:00.120
<b>- 花圃? - 是的
<b>- A garden? - Yes.</b></b>


146
00:20:04.160 --> 00:20:09.880
<b>所以你忍心丢我一个人在这儿吐口水吗?
<b>So you just leave me in the lurch with that slobber?</b></b>


147
00:20:27.640 --> 00:20:29.480
<b>谢了
<b>So.</b></b>


148
00:20:35.280 --> 00:20:38.000
<b>你会想我吗?
<b>Are you going to miss me?</b></b>


149
00:20:39.120 --> 00:20:42.480
<b>当然 就像脑袋上的包总得挠挠
<b>Yes, as much as a hole in the head.</b></b>


150
00:21:52.320 --> 00:21:54.970
<b>- 你 买种子? - 是的 帕特
<b>- Frog? - Yes.</b></b>


151
00:21:55.000 --> 00:21:59.440
<b>- 你会种地? - 不会 之前没弄过
<b>- You don't usually buy seeds. - No.</b></b>


152
00:22:00.920 --> 00:22:04.760
<b>- 你确定要买? - 是的 有些啥?
<b>- Are you sure? - Yes. Do you have some or what?</b></b>


153
00:22:06.080 --> 00:22:08.330
<b>我有...
<b>I have...</b></b>


154
00:22:08.360 --> 00:22:13.400
<b>豌豆、卷心菜 还有胡萝卜和其他小菜
<b>horse beans, cabbage. There are also carrots and other trifles.</b></b>


155
00:22:44.600 --> 00:22:47.530
<b>我想弄个自己的小花园
<b>I want to plant my own garden.</b></b>


156
00:22:47.560 --> 00:22:51.290
<b>种点作物 比如金灿灿的麦子
<b>A little poplar, maybe golden rice.</b></b>


157
00:22:51.320 --> 00:22:54.930
<b>我喜欢你这里金黄色的麦浪
<b>Like the yellow wave you have out there.</b></b>


158
00:22:54.960 --> 00:22:57.680
<b>种地要会除草 芬巴
<b>Golden rice is a weed, Finbar.</b></b>


159
00:23:00.440 --> 00:23:04.120
<b>我不懂 但我可以找个老师
<b>I had no idea. I could use a teacher.</b></b>


160
00:23:06.080 --> 00:23:10.320
<b>- 味道如何? - 我喜欢 美食还有陪伴
<b>- Does it taste good enough? - I enjoy both the food and the company.</b></b>


161
00:23:12.720 --> 00:23:17.040
<b>你的妻子做饭好吃吗? 是叫玛格丽特 对吗?
<b>Was your wife good at cooking? It was Margaret, wasn't it?</b></b>


162
00:23:20.600 --> 00:23:23.920
<b>- 对不起 我不是故意提…  - 不不不 没关系
<b>- Sorry... - It doesn't matter.</b></b>


163
00:23:24.600 --> 00:23:29.130
<b>只是 好久没听人提起她的名字了
<b>It's just been so long since anyone said her name.</b></b>


164
00:23:29.160 --> 00:23:30.880
<b>玛格丽特
<b>Margaret.</b></b>


165
00:23:31.680 --> 00:23:35.290
<b>她总爱实验新鲜玩艺儿
<b>She was always experimenting.</b></b>


166
00:23:35.320 --> 00:23:38.730
<b>她烤了个蛋糕 好久之前的事了
<b>She baked a cake... It's been a long time.</b></b>


167
00:23:38.760 --> 00:23:41.920
<b>她在里面放了苹果和坚果
<b>She put apples and nuts in it.</b></b>


168
00:23:42.640 --> 00:23:46.530
<b>还放了点肉桂 很独特的味道
<b>And a little bit of cinnamon. I have never tasted anything like it.</b></b>


169
00:23:46.560 --> 00:23:50.810
<b>- 听起来很美味 - 不 见鬼 超可怕的
<b>- It sounds delicious. - No, damn it. It was terrifying.</b></b>


170
00:23:50.840 --> 00:23:54.730
<b>我说过 闻所未闻的味道
<b>Like I said, I've never tasted anything like it.</b></b>


171
00:23:54.760 --> 00:23:57.850
<b>谢天谢地 她再也没这么做过
<b>Fortunately, I never got around to it again.</b></b>


172
00:23:57.870 --> 00:23:59.450
<b>当时是在都柏林吗?
<b>Was it in Dublin?</b></b>


173
00:23:59.480 --> 00:24:00.890
<b>对 是的
<b>And.</b></b>


174
00:24:00.920 --> 00:24:04.530
<b>每天我都会路过 她工作的书店
<b>Every day I passed by the bookstore where she worked.</b></b>


175
00:24:04.560 --> 00:24:08.210
<b>在去工厂的路上 你懂的 她真的很喜欢书
<b>On the way to the factory. How she loved those books though.</b></b>


176
00:24:08.240 --> 00:24:13.290
<b>- 她吸引了我的关注 - 我真希望能见到她
<b>- She got me interested. - I wish I had met her.</b></b>


177
00:24:13.320 --> 00:24:17.240
<b>她对我很好 就像你一样
<b>She was too good for me. Just like you.</b></b>


178
00:24:24.760 --> 00:24:27.600
<b>我去看看他
<b>I look right at him.</b></b>


179
00:24:39.960 --> 00:24:42.040
<b>嘿 莫娅
<b>Hey Moya.</b></b>


180
00:24:42.800 --> 00:24:47.410
<b>如果鱼上钩了 千万要小心 渔线会割伤手
<b>If you get a red skull on the hook, be careful because the line can cut your hand.</b></b>


181
00:24:47.440 --> 00:24:50.200
<b>来 用这个
<b>Here. Use it here.</b></b>


182
00:24:50.960 --> 00:24:53.000
<b>这样就好了
<b>Such.</b></b>


183
00:24:57.040 --> 00:25:00.930
<b>你想钓什么? 金鱼吗?
<b>What are you hoping to capture? A goldfish?</b></b>


184
00:25:00.960 --> 00:25:05.250
<b>- 把它带回家 起个名字叫戈尔迪 - 鱼没有情感
<b>- Take it home and call it Goldie. - A fish doesn't like one.</b></b>


185
00:25:05.280 --> 00:25:09.970
<b>我死去的老爹说过 不要枉费时间在不爱你的事物身上
<b>My dead father said you shouldn't love those who don't love you.</b></b>


186
00:25:10.000 --> 00:25:14.560
<b>- 很有道理 - 有人叫我去吃晚饭
<b>- It may be true. - I was told to catch dinner.</b></b>


187
00:25:18.440 --> 00:25:20.490
<b>咬钩了
<b>You have bite.</b></b>


188
00:25:20.520 --> 00:25:23.080
<b>拉紧渔线 拉紧渔线
<b>Give it some string.</b></b>


189
00:25:26.440 --> 00:25:28.880
<b>不
<b>No!</b></b>


190
00:25:34.640 --> 00:25:37.440
<b>莫娅 没事的 莫娅
<b>Moya! It does not matter.</b></b>


191
00:25:44.760 --> 00:25:46.760
<b>你在这儿 上帝保佑</b>

192
00:25:57.800 --> 00:25:59.920
<b>你好 帕特
<b>Hello, Pat.</b></b>


193
00:26:03.640 --> 00:26:04.820
<b>你好 西妮娅
<b>Hello, Sinéad.</b></b>


194
00:26:04.840 --> 00:26:08.410
<b>芬巴 什么风把你给吹来的?
<b>What are you doing here on a busy evening?</b></b>


195
00:26:08.440 --> 00:26:11.890
<b>- 凯瑟琳 - 芬巴 他今晚脾气有点不好
<b>- Catherine. - Finbar. He is grumpy tonight.</b></b>


196
00:26:11.920 --> 00:26:16.730
<b>- 那个老狗日的?不多见啊 - 是啊 尤其是今晚我还不当班
<b>- The old slambert? Never in my life. - And then on my night out.</b></b>


197
00:26:16.760 --> 00:26:21.050
<b>给老狗上一大杯啤的 再给他可怜的老婆来杯发泡酒
<b>A big dish for the grumpy stodder, a Babycham for his suffering wife -</b></b>


198
00:26:21.080 --> 00:26:23.690
<b>还有我的黑布林威士忌 谢啦
<b>- and a Black Bush for me.</b></b>


199
00:26:23.720 --> 00:26:28.610
<b>你卖那几本破书的钱可经不起这么糟践
<b>You're probably throwing money around. How can you make a living selling books?</b></b>


200
00:26:28.640 --> 00:26:32.040
<b>只要我还能赢钱 就没问题
<b>As long as I win money from you, I'll be fine.</b></b>


201
00:26:33.680 --> 00:26:37.730
<b>- 抓到开车的疯子了吗?  - 完全没头绪
<b>- Did you catch the speed devil? - Not at all.</b></b>


202
00:26:37.760 --> 00:26:42.050
<b>运气不好 但我会逮到他的
<b>I haven't had much luck, but I'll probably get hold of him.</b></b>


203
00:26:42.080 --> 00:26:44.760
<b>必须的
<b>I believe so.</b></b>


204
00:26:54.520 --> 00:26:56.290
<b>水 谢谢
<b>Water, please.</b></b>


205
00:26:56.320 --> 00:26:59.450
<b>- 拉得很棒 孩子  - 谢谢 我的朋友
<b>- Great game. - Thank you my friend.</b></b>


206
00:26:59.480 --> 00:27:03.650
<b>这是首老歌 寓意是青山不老春常在
<b>It's an old tune. Old as the mountains, but it's always good.</b></b>


207
00:27:03.680 --> 00:27:08.280
<b>- 你怎么看?  - 当"表演"那么看  - 是啊
<b>- Do you say old as the mountains? - We call it a gig.</b></b>


208
00:27:08.800 --> 00:27:11.930
<b>- 谢谢 - 你在这里干什么?
<b>- Thanks. - What are you doing over here?</b></b>


209
00:27:11.960 --> 00:27:15.650
<b>很久以前 一个爱尔兰人来到我的村子
<b>Long ago an Irishman came to my village.</b></b>


210
00:27:15.680 --> 00:27:18.850
<b>他演奏的曲子无比优美
<b>He played the most beautiful tune I have ever heard.</b></b>


211
00:27:18.880 --> 00:27:22.690
<b>但我错过了 所以我就跟来了这里
<b>He left before I learned it, so I just had to come.</b></b>


212
00:27:22.720 --> 00:27:26.090
<b>你不想念吗? 你的家乡?
<b>Don't you miss it? Your home country?</b></b>


213
00:27:26.120 --> 00:27:30.480
<b>战争和鲜血 我都不想念
<b>I don't miss the games. And I don't miss the blood.</b></b>


214
00:27:35.120 --> 00:27:38.530
<b>我看到莫娅桥上钓鱼 说在那边吃晚饭
<b>I saw your Moya fishing for dinner by the bridge.</b></b>


215
00:27:38.560 --> 00:27:42.890
<b>听上去像是她 有主意的很
<b>Sounds like her. She is very opinionated.</b></b>


216
00:27:42.920 --> 00:27:45.930
<b>我们就像黑夜中擦舷而过的小舟
<b>We are like ships that meet in the night.</b></b>


217
00:27:45.960 --> 00:27:49.170
<b>- 别对她太苛刻 - 还看到啥了?
<b>- Don't be too hard on her. - What have you?</b></b>


218
00:27:49.200 --> 00:27:53.040
<b>装渔具的箱子掉水里了
<b>The box of food fell into the water.</b></b>


219
00:27:53.760 --> 00:27:57.000
<b>- 什么? - 我讲话分散了她的注意力
<b>- What? - I talked and distracted her.</b></b>


220
00:27:58.000 --> 00:28:01.160
<b>好吧 多谢提醒
<b>Thanks for the warning.</b></b>


221
00:28:05.240 --> 00:28:10.080
<b>- 小心我的脚 - 早就不会踩了
<b>- Watch my feet. - It's been a hundred years. Quiet now.</b></b>


222
00:28:39.160 --> 00:28:41.720
<b>这一幕似曾相识啊
<b>I know that look.</b></b>


223
00:28:43.040 --> 00:28:49.010
<b>你要去哪儿? 我猜不会是因为鱼食掉水里了想跑吧?
<b>Where are you going? I guess you're not running away because of the food. Do you?</b></b>


224
00:28:49.040 --> 00:28:52.040
<b>我跟你妈妈讲了 都是我的错
<b>I told your mother it was my fault.</b></b>


225
00:28:55.000 --> 00:28:59.410
<b>你要是骑马跑了的话 你妈妈会很想你的
<b>She's going to miss you terribly when she's left here -</b></b>


226
00:28:59.440 --> 00:29:01.800
<b>我也会很孤单
<b>- as you ride away.</b></b>


227
00:29:03.600 --> 00:29:07.840
<b>你是个勇敢的孩子 莫娅 但马不爱走夜路
<b>You are brave, Moya. Because horses don't like the dark.</b></b>


228
00:29:09.720 --> 00:29:13.970
<b>他们害怕路上的坑洼和突然闪现的小动物
<b>They are terrified of the rabbit holes and the rabbits.</b></b>


229
00:29:14.000 --> 00:29:17.170
<b>所以最好在白天跑
<b>Better run away during the day -</b></b>


230
00:29:17.200 --> 00:29:21.330
<b>这样就不会遇到意想不到的事情
<b>- so you don't run into anything unexpected.</b></b>


231
00:29:21.360 --> 00:29:24.920
<b>当然 一切都随你
<b>But it's up to you. You decide.</b></b>


232
00:29:43.720 --> 00:29:46.690
<b>- 你还住在大篷车里吗? - 是的
<b>- Do you still live in the caravan? - Yes.</b></b>


233
00:29:46.720 --> 00:29:49.560
<b>妈妈说房子总也建不起来
<b>Mother says the house will never be finished.</b></b>


234
00:29:51.920 --> 00:29:56.290
<b>- 快走吧  - 什么?
<b>- Just go now. - What?</b></b>


235
00:29:56.320 --> 00:30:00.690
<b>- 作为一名绅士怎么能把女士拉在门口呢  - 不用了
<b>A gentleman always follows the lady right to the door.</b></b>


236
00:30:00.720 --> 00:30:05.050
<b>莫娅 该死的 你去哪儿了? 我饿死了
<b>Moya, damn it! Where have you been? I'm starving.</b></b>


237
00:30:05.080 --> 00:30:06.810
<b>这是谁?
<b>Who is it?</b></b>


238
00:30:06.840 --> 00:30:10.090
<b>- 一位绅士 - 喜欢柯蒂斯叔叔吗?
<b>- A gentleman. - Like Uncle Curtis here?</b></b>


239
00:30:10.120 --> 00:30:14.600
<b>- 你不是我叔叔 - 好好讲话 听懂了没有?
<b>- You are not my uncle. - Speak properly. Are you following?</b></b>


240
00:30:18.160 --> 00:30:21.240
<b>女人 烦死个人
<b>Women! They really can't stand it.</b></b>


241
00:30:56.840 --> 00:30:59.290
<b>流浪汉终于回来了
<b>The Wanderer is back.</b></b>


242
00:30:59.320 --> 00:31:02.890
<b>- 到时候了 - 我已经紧赶慢赶了
<b>- It was about time. - I just waited a bit.</b></b>


243
00:31:02.920 --> 00:31:07.490
<b>- 这是什么鬼? 苹果? - 我只能弄到这个
<b>- What the hell is this? Apples? - That's what I got.</b></b>


244
00:31:07.520 --> 00:31:10.890
<b>三个小时 就弄回来点苹果 你在搞什么鬼?
<b>After three hours you come with apples. What are you thinking?</b></b>


245
00:31:10.920 --> 00:31:15.250
<b>- 闭嘴  - 他怎么会是你哥哥?
<b>- Shut up! - How can he be your brother?</b></b>


246
00:31:15.280 --> 00:31:20.040
<b>- 口音都不一样 - 不关你的事
<b>- You don't even sound alike. - It is none of your business.</b></b>


247
00:31:21.880 --> 00:31:24.930
<b>- 你怎么搞的? - 我在大篷车里等莫娅
<b>- What have you done? - I was waiting for Moya.</b></b>


248
00:31:24.960 --> 00:31:28.170
<b>你不一定非要见她
<b>You don't have to be there.</b></b>


249
00:31:28.200 --> 00:31:32.400
<b>去拿了东西就回来 明白吗?
<b>Just get what we need and come back. Are you following?</b></b>


250
00:31:47.120 --> 00:31:49.730
<b>有人在吗
<b>Bank-bank.</b></b>


251
00:31:49.760 --> 00:31:53.930
<b>哦 是芬巴 谢谢
<b>Finbar, that is. Thanks.</b></b>


252
00:31:53.960 --> 00:31:56.570
<b>- 有点重 - 进来喝杯茶?
<b>- It's heavy. - A cup of tea?</b></b>


253
00:31:56.600 --> 00:31:58.800
<b>不了 谢谢
<b>No way.</b></b>


254
00:32:05.080 --> 00:32:07.280
<b>嘿 莫娅
<b>Hey Moya.</b></b>


255
00:32:10.480 --> 00:32:13.850
<b>- 你拿的是什么? - 没什么
<b>- What do you have there? - Nothing.</b></b>


256
00:32:13.880 --> 00:32:19.480
<b>- 也许我应该问问你妈妈 - 不 求你了 别跟他说
<b>- Maybe I should ask your mother. - No, you mustn't say anything to her.</b></b>


257
00:32:20.960 --> 00:32:25.880
<b>让我看看 让我看看
<b>Let me see. Come on.</b></b>


258
00:32:34.120 --> 00:32:36.680
<b>你从哪里得到的?
<b>Where did you get it from?</b></b>


259
00:32:37.880 --> 00:32:42.250
<b>- 你叔叔给你的? - 他不是我叔叔
<b>- Did your uncle give it to you? - He's not my uncle.</b></b>


260
00:32:42.280 --> 00:32:45.040
<b>他为什么给你这个?
<b>Why did he give it to you?</b></b>


261
00:32:47.040 --> 00:32:51.280
<b>他对你做了什么 你身上的瘀青怎么来的?
<b>Does it have anything to do with your bruises?</b></b>


262
00:32:52.840 --> 00:32:55.240
<b>莫娅
<b>Moya.</b></b>


263
00:32:56.640 --> 00:33:02.160
<b>发生了什么事? 你不想告诉我吗?
<b>Has something happened that you don't want to tell me about?</b></b>


264
00:33:06.000 --> 00:33:08.120
<b>怎么了?
<b>What?</b></b>


265
00:33:11.000 --> 00:33:12.600
<b>莫娅
<b>Moya!</b></b>


266
00:33:21.600 --> 00:33:27.680
<b>好绅士又来了 早上好啊西妮娅 莫娅
<b>There we have the good gentleman again. Good morning, Sinéad. Moya.</b></b>


267
00:33:30.440 --> 00:33:34.170
<b>你应该对西妮娅没兴趣吧 对你来说年轻了点
<b>You don't care about Sinéad, do you? She is legally young for you.</b></b>


268
00:33:34.200 --> 00:33:37.650
<b>闭嘴 柯蒂斯 别理他 他就是个混球
<b>Clap in, Curtis. Don't take care of him. He is a fool.</b></b>


269
00:33:37.680 --> 00:33:43.130
<b>咋了 我就不能和本地人聊两句吗? 交个朋友
<b>Now can't I even have a little chat with the locals? We are good friends.</b></b>


270
00:33:43.160 --> 00:33:47.010
<b>对不? 我就说嘛
